.(Main article: Marine Division Reconnaissance)
1st Reconnaissance Battalion (abbreviated as 1st Recon Bn) is a reconnaissance battalion in the United States Marine Corps. It is a stand-alone battalion with no parent regiment. Instead, it falls directly under the command of the 1st Marine Division. 1st Recon Bn is located at Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton in San Diego, California. 1st Recon Battalion was reactivated on July 5, 2000, as part of Marine Corps Commandant General James L. Jones' mission to revitalize Marine Corps reconnaissance.

Le 1er bataillon de reconnaissance des Marines ou simplement 1er bataillon de reconnaissance (1st Reconnaissance Battalion ou 1st Recon Bn) est un bataillon du Corps des Marines rattaché à la 1re division des Marines ainsi qu'au .
